{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017z75vgrFhQiihkqCmNFbvE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have all the information I need. Let me compile the comprehensive change/migration plan.\n\n**Summary of current state:**\n\n1. **Controller:** ingress-nginx v1.11.1\n   - Image: `registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.11.1@sha256:e6439a12b52076965928e83b7b56aae6731231677b01e81818bce7fa5c60161a`\n   - 1 replica, RollingUpdate (maxUnavailable=1)\n   - Resource requests are minimal (100m CPU, 90Mi memory) with no limits set\n   - Configured to run on nodes labeled `ingress-ready=true` and Linux systems, with tolerations for control-plane taints and zero termination grace period\n\n2. **Non-default controller args:**\n   - `--watch-ingress-without-class=true` — non-default\n   - `--enable-metrics=false` — non-default\n   - `--publish-status-address=localhost` — non-default (kind-specific)\n\n3. **ConfigMap configuration:**\n   - `allow-snippet-annotations: \"false\"` — was non-default in older versions but is now standard in 1.9+\n   - `limit-req-status-code: \"429\"` — intentionally set to return HTTP 429 instead of the default 503 for rate-limited requests\n\n4. **Services:**\n   - `ingress-nginx-controller`:\n   - NodePort 80:30754/TCP, 443:32077/TCP\n\n5. **Ingress resources:**\n   - `demo-app` with rewrite-target annotation\n   - `rate-api` configured with rate limiting (1 request per second, burst multiplier of 1)\n   - `rate-health` with no special annotations\n   - `canary-stable` and `canary-canary` for canary deployments, with the canary variant triggered by the X-Canary=always header\n   - `canary-alt` and `rate-api-alt-easy` as decoy resources marked for benchmarking\n\n6. **ValidatingWebhookConfiguration:**\n   - `ingress-nginx-admission` webhook with failurePolicy set to Fail and a CA bundle configured by the admission-patch job\n\n7. **RBAC setup:**\n   - ServiceAccounts and ClusterRoles for both ingress-nginx and ingress-nginx-admission with corresponding bindings\n\nNow I'm planning the upgrade path to v1.12.x, the next stable release after v1.11.1. I need to verify Kubernetes version compatibility (v1.12.x requires K8s 1.28+), review the changelog for any deprecated settings, and back up the current manifests. For flag compatibility, `--watch-ingress-without-class` should remain supported in v1.12.x without requiring changes.\n\nThe ConfigMap settings like `allow-snippet-annotations: false` and `limit-req-status-code: 429` need verification to ensure they're preserved during the upgrade, and all the nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io annotations including canary routing and rate limiting should remain stable across minor versions. The upgrade itself will use the existing rolling update strategy with just an image tag and digest update, followed by post-upgrade validation.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3829,"cache_read_input_tokens":37718,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3829},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b9bd144-0083-40e9-8402-c45a67a518ad","uuid":"57367668-4824-4fa4-a12b-2508a502797c","request_id":"req_011Cc6nxGkJ3TxEbUeB1ooCg"}
