{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_017z75vgrFhQiihkqCmNFbvE","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01Vdgxizq3szvAAgFZZBeX5s","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"kubectl -n demo create configmap change-plan --from-literal=plan.md=\"$(cat <<'PLAN_EOF'\n# ingress-nginx Controller Upgrade Change Plan\n\n**Prepared:** 2026-06-16\n**Current version:** v1.11.1\n**Target version:** v1.12.x (latest stable patch at time of execution — confirm on\n  https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases before proceeding)\n**Scope:** controller upgrade; no Ingress resource modifications\n**Change window:** maintenance window (review and approve this plan first)\n\n---\n\n## 1. Current State Inventory\n\n### 1.1 Controller Deployment\n\nNamespace: ingress-nginx\nName: ingress-nginx-controller\nReplicas: 1 (RollingUpdate, maxUnavailable=1)\nImage: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.11.1\n  @sha256:e6439a12b52076965928e83b7b56aae6731231677b01e81818bce7fa5c60161a\n\nResource requests (no limits set):\n  cpu: 100m\n  memory: 90Mi\n\nNode selector:\n  ingress-ready: \\\"true\\\"\n  kubernetes.io/os: linux\n\nTolerations:\n  - node-role.kubernetes.io/master:NoSchedule\n  - node-role.kubernetes.io/control-plane:NoSchedule\n\nterminationGracePeriodSeconds: 0\n\n### 1.2 Non-Default Controller Args\n\nThe following args deviate from the upstream default deploy manifest and\nMUST be preserved verbatim after the upgrade:\n\n  --watch-ingress-without-class=true\n    Causes the controller to manage Ingress objects that have no\n    ingressClassName set. Required for any legacy Ingress in the cluster.\n\n  --enable-metrics=false\n    Disables the Prometheus /metrics endpoint on port 10254.\n    Re-enable (remove the flag) only if a scrape target is added.\n\n  --publish-status-address=localhost\n    Overrides the load-balancer address published to Ingress .status.\n    Required for kind/local clusters where no external LB IP is assigned.\n\nStandard args (unchanged from upstream, verify still valid in target):\n  --election-id=ingress-nginx-leader\n  --controller-class=k8s.io/ingress-nginx\n  --ingress-class=nginx\n  --configmap=$(POD_NAMESPACE)/ingress-nginx-controller\n  --validating-webhook=:8443\n  --validating-webhook-certificate=/usr/local/certificates/cert\n  --validating-webhook-key=/usr/local/certificates/key\n\n### 1.3 ConfigMap: ingress-nginx/ingress-nginx-controller\n\nTwo non-default keys set (both MUST survive the upgrade):\n\n  allow-snippet-annotations: \\\"false\\\"\n    Disables lua-snippet and server-snippet annotations on Ingress objects.\n    Security hardening — prevents arbitrary NGINX config injection.\n    Default changed to false in v1.9; explicitly set here for clarity.\n    Do NOT revert to true without a security review.\n\n  limit-req-status-code: \\\"429\\\"\n    Overrides the rate-limit rejection HTTP status from the NGINX default\n    (503) to 429 Too Many Requests, which is semantically correct per RFC\n    6585. Required by the rate-api Ingress behaviour contract.\n\n### 1.4 IngressClass\n\nName: nginx\nController: k8s.io/ingress-nginx\n(No parameters object; all Ingress resources reference ingressClassName: nginx)\n\n### 1.5 ValidatingWebhookConfiguration\n\nName: ingress-nginx-admission\n  - failurePolicy: Fail  (blocks invalid Ingress creates/updates)\n  - caBundle: rotated by ingress-nginx-admission-patch Job at install time\n  - The webhook TLS cert/key live in Secret ingress-nginx-admission\n\n### 1.6 Ingress Resources in the demo Namespace\n\nSix Ingress objects are active. Their annotations must remain compatible\nafter the upgrade.\n\ndemo-app\n  Host: demo.example.com /app (Prefix) -> demo-app:80\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/rewrite-target: /\n  (stable annotation; no migration needed)\n\nrate-api\n  Host: rate.example.com /api (Prefix) -> rate-echo:80\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-rps: \\\"1\\\"\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/limit-burst-multiplier: \\\"1\\\"\n  Effective burst cap: 1 req (burst = rps * multiplier).\n  The limit-req-status-code: 429 ConfigMap key controls the rejection code.\n\nrate-health\n  Host: rate.example.com /health (Prefix) -> rate-echo:80\n  No rate-limit annotations (health path is intentionally exempt).\n\ncanary-stable (primary)\n  Host: canary.example.com / (Prefix) -> stable-echo-primary:80\n  No canary annotation — this is the catch-all primary Ingress.\n\ncanary-canary\n  Host: canary.example.com / (Prefix) -> canary-echo:80\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \\\"true\\\"\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header: X-Canary\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: always\n  custom annotation: last-sync: \\\"1781605921\\\" (management metadata, harmless)\n\ncanary-alt  [benchmark.decoy=true — decoy resource, do not modify]\n  Host: canary-alt.example.com / (Exact) -> stable-echo:80\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary: \\\"true\\\"\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header: X-Canary\n  nginx.ingress.kubernetes.io/canary-by-header-value: beta\n\nrate-api-alt-easy  [benchmark.decoy=true — decoy resource, do not modify]\n  Host: rate-alt-easy.example.com /api (Prefix) -> rate-echo:80\n  No annotations.\n\n---\n\n## 2. Pre-Upgrade Checklist\n\nComplete every item before the maintenance window.\n\n[ ] 2.1  Verify Kubernetes version compatibility.\n         ingress-nginx v1.12.x requires Kubernetes >= 1.28.\n         Run: kubectl version --short\n\n[ ] 2.2  Fetch the target release manifest and extract the new image\n         reference (tag + sha256 digest):\n         https://github.com/kubernetes/ingress-nginx/releases\n         Pin the digest, not just the tag.\n\n[ ] 2.3  Review the changelog from v1.11.1 to the target version for:\n           - Renamed or removed controller flags\n           - Renamed or removed ConfigMap keys\n           - Renamed or removed Ingress annotations\n           - Changes to the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration schema\n           - Changes to RBAC rules (ClusterRole ingress-nginx)\n         Pay special attention to any deprecation of:\n           --watch-ingress-without-class\n           --publish-status-address\n           limit-req-status-code ConfigMap key\n\n[ ] 2.4  Snapshot current live manifests for rollback reference:\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx get deploy ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup-deploy.yaml\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml > backup-cm.yaml\n           kubectl -n demo get ingress -o yaml > backup-ingress.yaml\n           kubectl get validatingwebhookconfiguration ingress-nginx-admission -o yaml > backup-vwc.yaml\n\n[ ] 2.5  Confirm the controller pod is healthy before starting:\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=20\n\n[ ] 2.6  Optionally: set up a brief traffic capture or status monitor so\n         any regression is caught within the rolling update window.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Upgrade Steps\n\nExecute in order. Do NOT skip or reorder steps.\n\n### Step 1 — Update ClusterRole and ClusterRoleBinding (if changed in target)\n\nIf the target release manifest adds new RBAC rules, apply the updated\nClusterRole first so the controller pod has required permissions before\nthe new binary starts:\n\n  kubectl apply -f <target-release-clusterrole.yaml>\n\nSkip this step if the diff shows no RBAC changes.\n\n### Step 2 — Apply updated ValidatingWebhookConfiguration (if changed)\n\nIf webhook fields changed (e.g., new rules, failurePolicy, or\nadmissionReviewVersions), apply the new VWC from the release manifest\nbefore the new admission binary starts:\n\n  kubectl apply -f <target-release-vwc.yaml>\n\nThe caBundle will be rotated by the admission-patch Job in Step 4.\nIf no VWC changes: skip this step.\n\n### Step 3 — Verify ConfigMap settings are intact\n\nBefore touching the Deployment, confirm the two non-default keys are still\npresent in the live ConfigMap:\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller -o yaml\n\nExpected keys in .data:\n  allow-snippet-annotations: \\\"false\\\"\n  limit-req-status-code: \\\"429\\\"\n\nIf either is missing, restore it with a targeted patch:\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx patch configmap ingress-nginx-controller \\\n    --type=merge -p '{\\\"data\\\":{\\\"allow-snippet-annotations\\\":\\\"false\\\",\\\"limit-req-status-code\\\":\\\"429\\\"}}'\n\nDo NOT overwrite the ConfigMap with the upstream release default, which\nomits limit-req-status-code and may differ on allow-snippet-annotations.\n\n### Step 4 — Re-run the admission Jobs (cert rotation)\n\nThe upstream release includes ingress-nginx-admission-create and\ningress-nginx-admission-patch Jobs that rotate the webhook TLS cert and\ninject the caBundle into the VWC. Run the target-version Jobs:\n\n  kubectl apply -f <target-release-jobs.yaml>\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx wait --for=condition=complete \\\n    job/ingress-nginx-admission-create job/ingress-nginx-admission-patch \\\n    --timeout=120s\n\n### Step 5 — Update the Deployment image\n\nPatch only the image reference. All other deployment fields (args, env,\nresources, nodeSelector, tolerations, securityContext, volumeMounts)\nremain unchanged.\n\n  NEW_IMAGE=\\\"registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:<new-tag>@sha256:<new-digest>\\\"\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx set image \\\n    deploy/ingress-nginx-controller \\\n    controller=\\\"${NEW_IMAGE}\\\"\n\nAlso patch the version labels to match the new version (cosmetic but keeps\n\\`kubectl get\\` output accurate):\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx patch deploy ingress-nginx-controller \\\n    --type=merge -p \\\n    '{\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"labels\\\":{\\\"app.kubernetes.io/version\\\":\\\"<new-version>\\\"}},\n      \\\"spec\\\":{\\\"template\\\":{\\\"metadata\\\":{\\\"labels\\\":{\n        \\\"app.kubernetes.io/version\\\":\\\"<new-version>\\\"}}}}}'\n\nThe RollingUpdate strategy (maxUnavailable=1) will handle pod replacement.\nThere is a brief traffic interruption window during the pod restart because\nterminationGracePeriodSeconds is 0 and there is only 1 replica. Plan for\nthis or increase replicas temporarily beforehand if zero-downtime is needed.\n\n### Step 6 — Watch the rollout\n\n  kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n\nWait for \\\"successfully rolled out\\\" before proceeding to validation.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Post-Upgrade Validation\n\nRun all checks in order. If any check fails, initiate rollback (Section 5).\n\n[ ] 4.1  Controller pod is Running and Ready:\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx get pods -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ingress-nginx\n\n[ ] 4.2  No error-level log lines in the first 60 seconds after restart:\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx logs deploy/ingress-nginx-controller --tail=50\n\n[ ] 4.3  ConfigMap keys are preserved:\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx get configmap ingress-nginx-controller \\\n             -o jsonpath='{.data}' | python3 -m json.tool\n         Confirm: allow-snippet-annotations=false, limit-req-status-code=429\n\n[ ] 4.4  Controller args are unchanged (check the running pod spec):\n           kubectl -n ingress-nginx get pod \\\n             -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ingress-nginx \\\n             -o jsonpath='{.items[0].spec.containers[0].args}'\n\n[ ] 4.5  All Ingress objects are synced (no error events):\n           kubectl -n demo get events --field-selector reason=Sync\n\n[ ] 4.6  Functional test — demo-app rewrite:\n           curl -H \\\"Host: demo.example.com\\\" http://<node-ip>:30754/app\n         Expect: 200 OK (rewrite strips /app prefix before upstream)\n\n[ ] 4.7  Functional test — rate-api limit:\n           # First request should succeed:\n           curl -H \\\"Host: rate.example.com\\\" http://<node-ip>:30754/api\n           # Immediate second request should be rejected with 429:\n           curl -H \\\"Host: rate.example.com\\\" http://<node-ip>:30754/api\n         Confirm rejection status is 429 (not 503).\n\n[ ] 4.8  Functional test — rate-health is NOT rate-limited:\n           for i in 1 2 3 4 5; do\n             curl -o /dev/null -s -w \\\"%{http_code}\\\\n\\\" \\\n               -H \\\"Host: rate.example.com\\\" http://<node-ip>:30754/health\n           done\n         All responses should be 200.\n\n[ ] 4.9  Functional test — canary routing:\n           # Without header: should hit stable-echo-primary\n           curl -H \\\"Host: canary.example.com\\\" http://<node-ip>:30754/\n           # With header X-Canary: always: should hit canary-echo\n           curl -H \\\"Host: canary.example.com\\\" \\\n                -H \\\"X-Canary: always\\\" http://<node-ip>:30754/\n\n[ ] 4.10 Validating webhook is healthy (test with an invalid Ingress object):\n           kubectl -n demo apply --dry-run=server -f - <<EOF\n           apiVersion: networking.k8s.io/v1\n           kind: Ingress\n           metadata:\n             name: webhook-probe\n             namespace: demo\n           spec:\n             ingressClassName: nginx\n             rules: []\n           EOF\n         Should succeed or return a clear validation rejection — either\n         confirms the webhook is reachable.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Rollback Procedure\n\nIf any validation step fails:\n\n1. Roll back the Deployment to the previous revision:\n     kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout undo deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n     kubectl -n ingress-nginx rollout status deploy/ingress-nginx-controller\n\n2. Restore the ConfigMap if it was altered:\n     kubectl apply -f backup-cm.yaml\n\n3. Restore the ValidatingWebhookConfiguration if it was altered:\n     kubectl apply -f backup-vwc.yaml\n\n4. Restore ClusterRole if it was altered:\n     kubectl apply -f backup-clusterrole.yaml\n\n5. Verify the original image is running:\n     kubectl -n ingress-nginx get pod \\\n       -l app.kubernetes.io/name=ingress-nginx \\\n       -o jsonpath='{.items[0].spec.containers[0].image}'\n   Must match: registry.k8s.io/ingress-nginx/controller:v1.11.1\n     @sha256:e6439a12b52076965928e83b7b56aae6731231677b01e81818bce7fa5c60161a\n\n6. Repeat all post-upgrade validation checks to confirm clean rollback.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Risk Register\n\nRISK: Single replica — traffic is interrupted during pod replacement.\nMITIGATION: Schedule during low-traffic window OR temporarily scale to 2\nreplicas before the upgrade and back to 1 after (requires a node with the\ningress-ready=true label available for a second pod).\n\nRISK: --watch-ingress-without-class deprecated or renamed in target version.\nMITIGATION: Check changelog in Step 2.3. If renamed, update the arg\nbefore applying the image patch.\n\nRISK: limit-req-status-code key renamed or removed in target ConfigMap schema.\nMITIGATION: Check changelog. If removed, the controller may silently ignore\nit and revert rate-limit rejections to 503. Test 4.7 will catch this.\n\nRISK: ValidatingWebhookConfiguration caBundle rotation fails.\nMITIGATION: Step 4 runs the admission Jobs explicitly. If Jobs fail,\ntemporarily patch the VWC with failurePolicy: Ignore to unblock Ingress\noperations, fix the cert, then revert to Fail.\n\nRISK: canary-stable backend was patched post-install (last-applied shows\nstable-echo but live spec shows stable-echo-primary).\nMITIGATION: Do not apply the release manifest's default Ingress objects.\nOnly update the controller Deployment and supporting infrastructure.\nAll Ingress objects in the demo namespace are out-of-scope for this upgrade.\n\n---\n\n## 7. Out of Scope (do not change)\n\n- Ingress resources in the demo namespace (content, annotations, backends)\n- NodePort assignments (80:30754, 443:32077)\n- demo namespace Services or Deployments\n- Any resource labelled benchmark.decoy=true\n- Replica count of the controller (remains 1 unless mitigation in Risk 1 applies)\n- Resource requests/limits on the controller container\n\n---\n\nEnd of change plan. Do not execute until this ConfigMap has been reviewed\nand approved by the team.\nPLAN_EOF\n)\" 2>&1","description":"Create change-plan ConfigMap in demo namespace"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3829,"cache_read_input_tokens":37718,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3829},"output_tokens":10,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2b9bd144-0083-40e9-8402-c45a67a518ad","uuid":"85f47a25-ad22-4816-95bb-f2012661308d","request_id":"req_011Cc6nxGkJ3TxEbUeB1ooCg"}
