{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QhDBiNFUryudhA9zefiBjd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `change-plan` ConfigMap is created in the `demo` namespace with a 15 KB `plan.md`. The cluster is untouched.\n\nHere's what the plan covers, derived entirely from the live cluster state:\n\n**Current state captured:**\n- Controller `v1.11.1`, 1 replica, RollingUpdate\n- **3 non-default controller args:** `--watch-ingress-without-class=true`, `--enable-metrics=false`, `--publish-status-address=localhost`\n- **2 non-default ConfigMap keys:** `allow-snippet-annotations: \"false\"` (security hardening), `limit-req-status-code: \"429\"` (RFC-correct rate-limit rejection code — the key detail that connects the ConfigMap to `rate-api`'s behaviour contract)\n- 6 Ingress objects: `demo-app` (rewrite), `rate-api`/`rate-health` (selective rate limiting), `canary-stable`/`canary-canary` (header-based canary routing), plus 2 decoy resources labelled `benchmark.decoy=true`\n- ValidatingWebhookConfiguration with `failurePolicy: Fail` and a rotated caBundle\n\n**Plan structure:**\n1. Pre-upgrade checklist (Kubernetes compat matrix, changelog review, manifest snapshots)\n2. Ordered upgrade steps: RBAC → VWC → ConfigMap verification → cert-rotation Jobs → image patch → rollout watch\n3. 10-point post-upgrade validation suite (including rate-limit 429 check and canary routing test)\n4. Rollback procedure referencing the exact current image digest\n5. Risk register (single-replica downtime window, flag deprecation, `limit-req-status-code` removal, webhook caBundle failure, the `canary-stable` backend drift between last-applied and live spec)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":154,"cache_read_input_tokens":47452,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":154},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","in